The paper describes a robot system designed for mobile manipulation tasks in inaccessible and dangerous environments, which falls under the scope of robotics (cs.RO). The system also includes advanced operator interfaces, which involve human-robot interaction and teleoperation, making it relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The robot's perception and manipulation capabilities involve the use of sensors and machine learning algorithms, which are related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the locomotion and manipulation functionalities on different levels of autonomy suggest that the system involves control and systems engineering (cs.SY).
